    138          //---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    139          /**
    140           * Restore the Milliseconds value from non-volatile memory.
    141           * On the ACU there are two possibilities after a reset:
    142           *  1. NVData recovered RAM variables
    143           *     In this case, the Milliseconds variable is restored to its value before the reset and
    144           *     it is ready for use. Also, all the non-volatile timers are restored and ready for use.
    145           *  2. NVData was unable to recover RAM variables
    146           *     In this case, the non-volatile timers were not restored either. Therefore, the value of
    147           *     the Milliseconds variable is probably 0 from the initialization firmware; but the value
    148           *     is actually unimportant. Any starting value will work since there are no active timers.
    149           *
    150           * On any non-ACU project type, the method of restoring the Milliseconds value must be managed
    151           * through the Millis_prv.h file using the following macros:
    152           *      RESTORE_HANDLER()
    153           *      INIT_COMPLETE()
    154           *      STORE_HANDLER()
    155           */

